# GitKraken MCP (Cursor)

Use **GitKraken MCP** for git status, branches, PRs, issues, and Launchpad when available.

## MCP servers (two sources — both valid)

| Source | Server id | Best for |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| GitLens extension | `user-eamodio.gitlens-extension-GitKraken` | Launchpad, graph, PR/issue UI, workspace list |
| gk CLI | `GitKraken` in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` | Same surface via `gk mcp --host=cursor` |

Prefer **GitLens extension** tools when both are enabled. Fall back to `gh` only if MCP is unavailable.

## Repo context

- **Workspace:** `modme-ui`
- **Repo:** `modme-ui-01` → `c:\Users\dylan\Monorepo_ModMe`
- **Canonical remote:** GitHub `Ditto190/modme-ui-01`; GitLab mirror optional

## Agent prompts that map to MCP tools

| User intent | Tool |
|-------------|------|
| What needs my attention? | `gitlens_launchpad` (pass repo `directory`) |
| Git status / diff / log | `git_status`, `git_log_or_diff` |
| Open PRs assigned to me | `pull_request_assigned_to_me` (`provider: github`) |
| Create or review PR | `pull_request_create`, `pull_request_create_review` |
| Issues assigned to me | `issues_assigned_to_me` |
| List workspaces | `gitkraken_workspace_list` |

Always pass `directory` as the absolute repo path (main checkout or active worktree).

## CLI (terminal)

```powershell
.\scripts\gitkraken\setup-cursor.ps1   # doctor + MCP install
gk ai commit                           # AI commit message
gk pr list                             # PRs in workspace
gk graph                               # terminal commit graph
```

Setup guide: `docs/gitkraken-cli-setup.md`
